
 NFS Pre-Requisites

1. nfs-utils package
    Required on the NFS server (and client)
    Provides NFS daemons and utilities

2. NFS service availability
    `nfs-server` service must be present
    Manages `nfsd`, `mountd`, `lockd`, and `statd`

3. Kernel support
    Linux kernel with NFS support enabled
    NFS kernel modules available

4. Network connectivity
    Client and server must have IP reachability

5. Required port
    TCP 2049 available for NFS traffic

6. Firewall / Security rules
    NFS allowed through system firewall
    Allowed in cloud security groups / NSGs (if used)

7. Storage readiness
    Local filesystem (XFS / EXT4)
    Directory prepared for export

